SkyrimReLive — friend install package
======================================

Quick start:

  1. Double-click  INSTALL.bat
     The installer walks you through the rest.

  2. Once installed, double-click  LAUNCH.bat  to play.

  3. To remove the mod later, double-click  UNINSTALL.bat


What's in this package
----------------------

  INSTALL.bat        Run this first. Checks dependencies, installs the plugin.
  LAUNCH.bat         Run this to play (after INSTALL succeeds).
  UNINSTALL.bat      Removes the SkyrimReLive plugin only (leaves SKSE etc).
  README.txt         This file.

  files\
    SkyrimReLive.dll      The plugin DLL
    SkyrimReLive.toml     Plugin config (preconfigured for {{HOST_NAME}}'s server: {{HOST_IP}})

  downloads\
    PUT_DOWNLOADS_HERE.txt   Read this. Drop the SKSE .7z and Address
                             Library .zip here BEFORE running INSTALL.bat
                             — the installer extracts and places them
                             for you automatically.

  scripts\
    install.ps1           Installer logic (called by INSTALL.bat)
    launch.ps1            Launcher (called by LAUNCH.bat)
    uninstall.ps1         Uninstaller (called by UNINSTALL.bat)


Tip: skip the "open browser, find files, copy by hand" step
-----------------------------------------------------------

The installer can do the SKSE and Address Library install for you if you
drop their downloaded archives into the  downloads\  folder BEFORE you
run INSTALL.bat.

  1. Download SKSE 2.2.6 (.7z) from https://skse.silverlock.org/
  2. Download "All in one (all game versions)" zip from
     https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/32444
  3. Drop both files (NOT extracted, just the original archive) into
     this bundle's  downloads\  folder.
  4. Run INSTALL.bat. It detects them and extracts/places them
     automatically. (It will install 7-Zip via winget if needed to
     handle the .7z.)

If you skip this and run INSTALL.bat without the downloads, it falls
back to opening the download pages and walking you through the manual
copy-paste path.


What you'll need
----------------

  Skyrim Special Edition on Steam, runtime 1.6.1170.

The installer will pop open download pages for these if you don't have them:

  - SKSE64 2.2.6        (https://skse.silverlock.org/)
  - Address Library     (https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/32444)
  - Tailscale           (the installer offers to install this for you via winget)


How to play
-----------

  1. {{HOST_NAME}} runs the SkyrimReLive server.
  2. You launch Skyrim via LAUNCH.bat.
  3. Load any save. Wait for the world to load.
  4. Press the tilde (~) key to open the in-game console.
  5. Type:    rl status
     You should see:    state=connected server={{HOST_IP}}:27015 player_id=N

If state is "idle" or "failed":
  - Check Tailscale is connected (tray icon should be green)
  - Check that {{HOST_NAME}} has the server running
  - Type:    rl connect    to retry


In-game console commands
------------------------

Press tilde (~) to open the console, then type:

  rl status               connection state, ghost count, packet stats
  rl connect              manually connect (if auto_connect is off)
  rl disconnect           cleanly close the connection
  rl cell                 show your current cell
  rl demo start           spawn a fake "ghost" orbiting you (solo test)
  rl demo stop            despawn the demo ghost
  rl help                 list all commands


What works right now
--------------------

  - See {{HOST_NAME}} as a ghost actor in the same cell as you.
  - Watch them walk, run, sneak.
  - See them draw / sheath weapons.
  - Smooth motion (100ms snapshot interpolation).

What doesn't work yet
---------------------

  - No combat damage between players.
  - No NPC sync — your bandits aren't their bandits.
  - No persistent inventory / quest state across sessions.
  - Other players currently look like a clone of YOUR character (custom
    appearance is on the roadmap).


Troubleshooting
---------------

"plugin SkyrimReLive.dll disabled, address library needs to be updated"
  Address Library isn't installed. Re-run INSTALL.bat — it'll send you
  to the Nexus page.

"timed out waiting for Welcome" in SkyrimReLive.log
  Either {{HOST_NAME}}'s server isn't running, Tailscale isn't connected,
  or you're behind a firewall blocking outgoing UDP. Tailscale fixes
  most cases — make sure the tray icon is green.

Skyrim crashes during save load
  Try a different save first to confirm. If that works, the original
  save may be incompatible (rare). If both crash, check that no other
  multiplayer mod (Skyrim Together Reborn) is installed alongside —
  they conflict.

Game freezes on connection
  Edit  Data\SKSE\Plugins\SkyrimReLive.toml
  Change:    auto_connect = true
  To:        auto_connect = false
  Then load the save and manually connect:    rl connect


Logs (if you need to send something to {{HOST_NAME}} for debugging)
-------------------------------------------------------------------

  C:\Users\<you>\Documents\My Games\Skyrim Special Edition\SKSE\
    SkyrimReLive.log     ← our plugin's log
    skse64.log           ← SKSE's log (look for SkyrimReLive lines)


